public interface ICacheableModel<T>
extends org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<T>

A Model that can be used for caching derived objects. It must implement a getKey() method that returns a cache key uniquely identifying the model object, and a getLastModified() method returning the model object's last modification time.

Method Summary

Method Detail

getLastModified

org.apache.wicket.util.time.Time getLastModified()
Return the time of the last update to the Model's object; or null if it won't ever change. When this changes, cached information based on this object needs to be updated.

getKey

Serializable getKey()
Return a hash key for this model's object. This is similar to hashCode() (and can even fall back on hashCode()), but must be done explicitly. This is because some implementations of hashCode() (e.g. HibernateObjectModel) rely on the existence of a datastore object. Changes to the underlying datastore can change the hashCode or throw a NullPointerException.
